    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that's exactly what people say when they don't want to believe it. it's always \"science fiction\" or \"unlikely\" until it actually happens. if they're using something like sonic frequencies or smart-home signals to bypass the conscious mind, wouldn't that be considered research? i just don't see how it could NOT be possible with how much data they have on us now. it feels like they've found a way to use our sleep cycles against us.",
