      "content": "The technology to influence sleep cycles using external signals is a very active area of scientific research, particularly in areas like brainwave entrainment. However, the leap from general research into a mass, targeted delivery of a specific jingle during your sleep is a massive and currently unproven claim. It is more probable that your mind is generating this intense, repetitive imagery as a form of psychological pattern recognition based on subtle, unconscious inputs from your environment.",
